Looking for some super easy ideas for your Game  Day spread? Look no further!🙌 Here are three delicious #LowCarb recipes that would be perfect for the Big Game! 🍕🌭😋
...
📝 Notes by Lori , @lori.monigold , the Amazing Chef 👩‍🍳:

1.🍕Crispy Pizza Pockets:

To make these grab your flatbreads, shredded cheese, some mini pepperonis( or regular pepperonis diced up small), and some marinara for dunking. Place flatbread on parchment and cover with a thin ayer of cheese. Microwave 30 seconds or until cheese is melty. Cut into four strips. Add pepperoni and cheese and fold into overlapping triangles until you reach the end (see video). Heat some oil in a skillet over medium heat and fry until golden and crisp, about 2-3 minutes per side. Place on paper towel lined plate to drain off any excess oil and serve with your favorite marinara or ranch dipping sauce.

2.🌭Cheesy Crunch Dogs:

To make these heat some oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add hot dogs and cook 4-6 minutes(Save oil for frying again). Remove to towel lined plate and prepare your flatbreads by cutting one sheet into four equal sections. Spread a thin layer of cream cheese on the edge furthest from you. Place one hot dog on each section of bread closest to you. Sprinkle cheese over bread between hot dog and cream cheese. Roll tightly and crisp in oiled pan over medium heat 3-4 minutes per side. These could also be done in an air fryer at 350 degrees for 6-8 minutes flipping half way through.

3.🔺Crispy Homemade Chips:

Cut your flatbreads into fourths and then into triangles. Heat oil over medium heat in a pot. Fry chips until golden and crisp watching closely as this only takes a few seconds. Enjoy with dips of choice like; guacamole, salsa, or queso.

📝Pro tip: Work with 1-2 flatbreads at a time keeping the rest sealed in bag to prevent drying of bread.
.
.

Happy #nationalpickleday !!..🤩
Here’s @annies_keto incredibly delicious Fried Pickle Chip recipe to celebrate this delicious day!!!🙌😍.
For all of the pickle lovers out there, this amazing recipe will become a staple in your #lowcarblife !!🥒🤯
...
Recipe and video credit: @Annies_keto. Thank you so much for the amazing recipe!🙏💕😊
...
Ingredients:
1/2 cup of full pickle chips
1 egg
3 sheets of @cutdacarb flatbreads
1 tbs pickle juice
1 tbs Old Bay seasoning
1 tbs garlic powder 
1 tsp pepper
...
Instructions: 
1. Dry out flatbreads in the oven at 200 degrees for 20 minutes.
2.  Break flatbreads into bread crumbs (by hand or blender). 3. Beat egg, pickle juice, seasonings and hot sauce (optional) to create egg wash. 
4. Dip each pickle into egg wash and then into bread crumbs (patting the crumbs in for a thick layer). 5. Shallow fry in your oil of choice. 
6. Fry each side until golden brown. 
7. Once removed from oil, sprinkle with Old Bay seasoning (optional). 8. Enjoy! .
.
.
.

Crispy, Low Carb, DELICIOUS!..👌😋
Stack’em Up and Enjoy’em #Guiltfree Like Naomi did!.. 🤩
.
.
.
Creator: @ketowats … Naomi, this looks out of this world delicious and thank you for sharing it with us!…🙏💕😍.
.
.
This was the best dish I’ve made so far using @cutdacarb flatbread. I used the equivalence of 1.2 serving of the sheet. I cut out the shapes from 2 flatbreads and kept the extra for chips some other time. Fried it in avocado oil (oil of preference, olive oil depending on the type can make it taste a little bitter). The meat mixture is just savory cooked ground beef mixed with cream cheese. I topped with melted cheddar cheese and repeated the steps till the top layer which I used melted mozzarella cheese, pickled jalapeños and sour cream. 

Dish was bomb. Have you tried @cutdacarb yet? Did you know that code “10off24” gives you 10% off your first 24 pack order and FREE SHIPPING? 

Happy Wednesday beautiful people! 🤎🤍🖤❤️.
.
.
.

Looking for the perfect #LowCarb celebratory spread to enjoy with family this weekend?🥳🎆…Look no further!🎉 Your 4th of July spread doesn’t have to be boring!🙌🤩.
…
🌭Cheesy Hot Dogs.
🥘Homemade Chips.
🍕Pepperoni Pizza Pockets.
…
✅For Hot Dogs:
1. Fry the franks.
2. Cut your flatbread in 4ths.
3. Add cream cheese to the sealing end to secure the roll.
4. Add franks and then cheese.
5. Roll and Fry.
...
✅For Pepperoni Pizza Pockets:
Repeat all steps for Hot Dogs, replacing franks with Pepperoni.
...
✅For Chips:
Cut the flatbreads in 4ths then cut in triangles and fry for few seconds .
Dips featured:
🍅 Salsa .
🥑 Guacamole .
🍃 Spinach Dip.
.
.
.

node.text:
Ever wondered how you can make the perfect shells for your Cut Da Carb Cannolis without a Cannoli Shell maker?!.. 🤔. Wonder no more!..Here, Allie is showing you all you need to know!.. 👏🙏😍.
✅About 2 Net Carbs for Each Cannoli !…😳
.
.
 #Repost @eat.keto.af .. Thank you Allie for the amazing creation and showing us this perfect and yet simple method for making these crunchy shells!..🙏😍💕 ・・・
The air fryer comes through! Such a great no-mess, no-fuss option for frying things. I thought @cutdacarb would work as cannoli shells and it did! So good! There is a little technique involved but overall it’s easy and comes together simply! A great snack or dessert for any time of day

Keto cannoli using @cutdacarb

INGREDIENTS
4 cannolis
// 1 sheet @cutdacarb flatbreads
// 1 egg, lightly beaten
// oil spray
// 15 oz ricotta
// 3 tbsp zero calorie sweetener + more for dusting
// 10 drops sweetener
// 3 squares sugar free 70% dark chocolate
// 24 sugar free semi-sweet chocolate chips

METHOD
1. Make 4 tinfoil molds. Watch my highlight for my homemade foil mold method!
2. Cut out 4 circles from the @cutdacarb flatbreads. I used the top of the 15 oz ricotta container for a stencil and it fit 4 rounds perfectly
3. Lightly spray the molds with some oil wrap each with a mold and seal with egg. Also brush all over with egg. Set seam side down to hold the seal
4. Spritz fryer and shells with oil and air fry 2 at a time at 400*F for 2 mins. Don’t overcook! Should be slightly darker than the plain flatbreads but not too golden
5. Let cool for 1 minute then remove tinfoil (my method in my IGTV video) and let fully cool
6. While shells are cooling, mix together ricotta, confectioners sweetener, and sweet drops
7. Melt chocolate in microwave, dip shell ends in, then set them in fridge for 5 mins on chopsticks
8. Put filling in piping bag or plastic bag with corner cut off. Piped into shell and add chocolate chops and a dusting of confectioners
9. Enjoy!

Oh how we all love crab Rangoons!..A perfect creamy and crispy bite!..👌😋
...
@mindfully.meghan .. Thank you so much for the amazing recipe and instructions!!🙏😍💕
・・・
crab rangoons using @cutdacarb for the first time!! I have to say I’m officially obsessed with cut-da-carb and I can’t wait to make more things with it! What is your favorite thing to make with it?? It crisped up perfectly and I was able to seal the edges quite easily using water - so so impressed!! As for the filling - it was delicious but not exactly what I was looking for when it comes to crab rangoons. I’d like to try using real crab meat and play with adding a sweetener next time. I’ll keep you posted when I come up with the perfect filling! After sealing the filling in the “shells” I brushed them with avocado oil and then cooked them in the air fryer at 380 for 5 minutes. It was the perfect amount of time! I just need to find the right filling now...

Many of you have been asking us to share @annies_keto incredibly delicious Fried Pickle Chip recipe and so here it is!!🙌😍 For all of the pickle lovers out there, this amazing recipe will become a staple in your #lowcarblife!!🥒🤯
...
Recipe and video credit: @Annies_keto. Thank you so much for the amazing recipe!🙏💕😊
...
Ingredients:
1/2 cup of full pickle chips
1 egg
3 sheets of @cutdacarb flatbreads
1 tbs pickle juice
1 tbs Old Bay seasoning
1 tbs garlic powder 
1 tsp pepper
...
Instructions: 
1. Dry out flatbreads in the oven at 200 degrees for 20 minutes.
2.  Break flatbreads into bread crumbs (by hand or blender). 3. Beat egg, pickle juice, seasonings and hot sauce (optional) to create egg wash. 
4. Dip each pickle into egg wash and then into bread crumbs (patting the crumbs in for a thick layer). 5. Shallow fry in your oil of choice. 
6. Fry each side until golden brown. 
7. Once removed from oil, sprinkle with Old Bay seasoning (optional). 8. Enjoy! .
.
.
.

✅One Flatbread can be cut into 5 sections and cut into 30 chips for ONLY 9 Grams of Net carbs! 😳❗️.... Have Your Chips and Eat them too😋
.
.
______
Instructions: ...
✅Method 1: FRYING
Bring a small pan of oil to high heat but not smoking point. Fry in small batches to get color consistency. They fry for less than 10 seconds. Drain excess oil on paper towel.
...
✅Method 2: BAKING
Arrange Chips on a piece of parchment paper or foil and then place in a baking pan. Coat with cooking oil and then season to your liking and bake at 350 for 5 to Maximum 10 minutes depending on your oven setting and power. *Keep an eye out as they color fast *
...
✅Method 3:MICROWAVE
Arrange Chips on a piece of parchment paper or paper towel, coat with cooking oil and then season to your liking and Microwave for 1 to Maximum 2 minutes depending on your microwave setting and power. *Keep an eye out as they color fast*

🍕Easy Peasy Pizza Pops, #LowCarbStyle !.
@lori.monigold Has Done it again! 
✅Less than 5g Net Carbs for 3 Pieces!!🤯
#LowCarb , #LowCalorie ,Super #Fun & #Delicious !.
📝Notes and Recipe by Lori:
Here is a super fun way to get your pizza fix and keep it low carb. These cheesy pizza pops come in at under 5 net carbs per stick and they are a breeze to make! Give them a try and let us know what you think🤗

🧀Ingredients:
2 Cut Da Carb flatbreads
5-6 string cheese sticks( I used Tis light string cheese)
2 tbsp cream cheese, softened
1/4 cup marinara sauce
1/4 cup shredded mozzarella

Optional: 
Mini pepperoni 
Grated parmesan 
Basil 

🔥Directions:

Preheat oven to 400*
1. Cut your flatbread lengthwise into thirds, stack the segments on top of each other and cut into thirds in the opposite direction to form even squares. Keep your flatbread in an airtight bag until you are ready to roll to prevent them from drying out. 
2. Cut your string cheese sticks into thirds. 
3. Spread a thin layer of cream cheese on one side edge of the flatbread and place the cheese in the center on the opposite side. There should be space to either side of the cheese to allow for spreading as the cheese melts. Roll tightly so that cream cheese edge seals the roll shut. 
4. Place 3-4 rolls on a wooded skewer and brush lightly with marinara sauce and sprinkle on some of the shredded cheese. Add on pepperoni or any other toppings you like. 
5. Bake 8-10 minutes and top with grated parmesan and basil. Enjoy dipped in marinara, ranch or some garlic butter!

❤️Hope Y’all enjoy!!!

⭐️Macros per pop:
Calories:153
Fat:6.9g
Protein:15.1g
Total Carbs:6.9g
Fiber:2.3g
Net Carbs:4.6g.
.
.
.
.

🔥🧀 Fried Raviolis, #LowCarbStyle.
🥇A Must Try for all Crispy & Cheesy Bite Lovers!👌🤤.

📝Notes by @lori.monigold , the talented creator of this amazing recipe!👏😋:
This super crispy lower carb version of this classic favorite is sure to have your taste buds screaming Mama Mia!!! I pan fried these in a little oil, however, I also ran a test batch in the air frier to be able to provide you with that option as well. Both were absolutely delicious and super crunchy! Here is how you make them…

🧀Ingredients:
2 @cutdacarb flatbreads
Filling:
1/2 cup ricotta cheese
1/2 cup mozzarella cheese
1/4 parmesan, shredded
Salt 
@flavorgod garlic lovers
2 tsp each chopped basil and parsley 
Egg for sealing 
Dredge:
2 eggs, whisked
1-1.5 cup grated parmesan

Oil for frying(I use extra light olive oil)
Marinara sauce for dipping

🔥Directions:
Combine all your filling ingredients into a bowl and mix well.
Lay out one Cut Da Carb flatbread and scoop the filling out evenly with a small cookie scoop in a 3x4 grid(see video).
Brush egg in between filling and around the border. Top with other flatbread and cut between filling into squares.
Add egg into one bowl and grated parmesan into another. Dunk each ravioli square into egg and then into parmesan. Squeeze all edges together to reinforce the seal. 
Add oil to skillet over medium heat. Pan fry ravioli 3 minutes per side or until golden and crisped. For the air fryer option cook at 350 4 minutes per side watching closely as they will brown fast. 
Drain on paper towel to remove excess oil and plate them up with more grated parmesan and basil. I like to dip mine in some warmed marinara sauce.

❤️Enjoy!!!

⚖️Macros for these :
Calories:89
Fat:5.5g
Protein6.5g
Net Carbs:2.3g
.

🍰 #NoSugarAdded , Raspberry Mascarpone Pizza.
Happy Saturday Y’all!💕
Sweet, Creamy and #Guiltfree !🤩😋. @chelle.does.keto , made this sweet treat, For our Pizza Contest !👏😍.
⁣…
⁣📝Notes by Michelle: 
⁣It's no secret that I have a sweet tooth so I thought this would be the perfect entry for #CutDaCarbPizza Contest Entry.
⁣I made some raspberry jam (raspberries, lemon 🍋 juice, and powdered allulose) - mashed and simmered the raspberries until it thickened. ⁣
⁣
Then I brushed the jam on the flatbread and baked it for about 6 minutes 375° then added my mascarpone (whipped mascarpone, powdered allulose, and sugar free caramel cheesecake syrup then topped with fresh raspberries, lemon 🍋 zest, and powdered sugar. 😊.
.
.
.
⁣ #lowcarb #lowcarbdiet #ww #wwdessert #iifym #diabeticrecipes #lowcarbrecipes #caloriedeficit #lowcalorie #lowcarbdesserts #lowcarbtreats #ketodessert #lowcarbsweets #ketodiet #sugarfree #sugarfreerecipes #cutdacarb #cutdacarbrecipes #cutdacarbwraps #cutdacarbdessert #nosugarrecipes #sugarfreedesserts #lowcarbtreats

Run to the kitchen and make these  Crispy & Cheesy Bites by: 
@megan71586 ..🔥😋👏.
✅Use Megan’s Code to Save:

📝Notes by Megan:

Do yourself a favor and make these ASAP. So crispy on the outside and filled with cheesy taco meat 🤤 

• Brown ground beef in a pan and seasoned with @porkkinggood new Taco Seasoning 

• In a big bowl add your ground beef, 28lbs of shredded cheese and 1/2c pico de Gallo .

• Take @cutdacarb flatbreads and cut them into long strips. I made mine about 2” thick lengthwise. 

• Next you’re going to add your filling to the bottom of one strip and fold it into a triangle. Keep folding up and the inside filling totally covered. I secure my ends with cream cheese. 

• After all triangles were made I deep fried them for about 1min or until golden brown. You can also fry them in a pan. 

• Top with taco ranch and dip in all the sour cream 

PROMO CODE for @porkkinggood : MEGANLOVESPORK .

node.text:
🔥Foot Long #CheeseStuffedCutDaCarbsub!

✅Only 11g Net Carbs for the Entire Sub!!🤩👏.
This cheesesteak is ginormous and is certainly enough to feed two.... but we won’t judge if you make it just for you🤗
It’s made with thinly sliced tender ribeye steak, ooey gooey melted provolone, and caramelized onions—all piled into a #cheesestuffedCutDaCarbsub !😋
…
📝Notes by @lori.monigold the amazing creator:

🥩 Ingredients: 

1Tbsp unsalted butter 
1 lb Ribeye steak trimmed and thinly sliced
1/2 tsp salt or to taste
1/2 tsp Black pepper or to taste
1 sweet onion (small), sliced
1tbsp brown sugar substitute 
3 slices provolone cheese
1 @cutdacarb flatbread 
Spray oil
1/2 cup shredded mozzarella 
1 Tbsp spicy mayonnaise or to taste. 

🔥 Directions:

Add butter to your pan/cooktop. Add onions and sweetener, sautéed until caramelized then transfer to a bowl or scoot to the side of pan.
Spread the thinly sliced steak in an even layer into the pan . Let brown for a couple of minutes undisturbed then flip and finish cooking. Stir in onions and season with  salt and  black pepper. 
Turn off heat and add cheese. Cover to melt using residual heat.
Make you sub by adding one cut da carb flatbread to a parchment lined baking sheet. Add on mozzarella in a thin layer and microwave 30 seconds. Fold in long edges to center of flatbread(see video) Toast in oven at 375 just a few minutes to crisp bread. 
Spread a thin layer of mayo on the your sub bun. Add the cheesy beef into your bun.
Serve warm and enjoy !!! 
.
.
.
.

🍕PULL APART PIZZA ROLL UPS #LowCarbStyle !..🔥@ketowithdeedee Aced These!👏.. So Crispy and Yummy!!😋.

✅Two Flavors:
1.Pepperoni & Sausage Pizza
2.Chicken Bacon Ranch Pizza
⁣…
📝Notes by DeeDee:
I seen my girl @kristysketolifestyle make these and knew I needed them! They are so easy to make too. I used my favorite @cutdacarb flatbreads to make these. I did two flavors since I couldn’t decide lol. One side is chicken bacon ranch pizza and the other side is pepperoni and sausage pizza. All you have to do is add you favorite ingredients to your @cutdacarb flatbread and roll them up. Slice into pieces and add to your greased pan. I baked mine for about 15 minutes at 375. ⁣
⁣
@cutdacarb is my favorite low carb flatbread! The whole bread is only 9 net carbs and 80 calories! Check them out if you haven’t already. I can’t wait to make these roll ups again and try some different flavors. ⁣
⁣What is your favorite low carb pizza substitute? What flavor of roll ups would you make?⁣.
.
.
.

node.text:
🌮🥗Low Carb Taco Salad, a perfect meal to celebrate this beloved #TacoTuesday ! 🍾🥳.
…
✅Each Foot Long Flatbread can produce up to 36 pieces of chips, for 9grams of Net Carbs!!🤩. 
💰New Coupon: Get 24 Freshly Baked Flatbreads for only $21.57 , including Free Shipping! Code: AUGUST10.

📝Notes by @ketobrawn , the awesome creators of this deliciousness:
Taco Salad.... ⠀
Shawn wanted a taco salad tonight... I gotchu boo !!! 😁😁⠀
Well, this was mine, hers was much smaller 🤣🤪😂⠀
We fried up some @cutdacarb chips for the crunch,  seasoned with @flavorgod Taco Tuesday seasoning right out of the oil. ⠀
This bad boy is piled with romaine and Iceberg lettuce, sharp shredded cheese, diced red onion, halved baby tomatoes, 1 sliced fresh jalapeno,  seasoned taco beef, sour cream,  and our homemade SF catalina dressing.. ✅The Catalina... ⠀
1/2 cup light olive oil ⠀
1/4 cup SF ketchup⠀
1/4 cup apple cider vinegar ⠀
1 tsp paprika ⠀
1/2 tbsp onion powder ⠀
1/2 tbsp worcestershire ⠀
1/4 cup powdered swerve⠀
We just added all this to a mason jar and shook the hell out of it... 😁😁⠀
This dressing is great on any salad,  easy to make, and so damn delicious 😋😋😋⠀
Almost Friday Brawnies !! Love y'all 💞❤🥰❤💞.
…
#cutdacarb #cutdacarbwraps #atkinsdiet #iifym #lchf #lowcarbdiet #lowcarb #lowcarbrecipes #lowcarbfoods #ketorecipes #ketofoods #lowcarbsnacks #ketomeals #cutdacarbrecipes #ketoidea  #lowcarbfood #ketotaco #lowcarbtaco #lowcarbbread #ketobrawn #lowcarbtacoshell #cico #cutdacarbchips 
⠀⠀
